events.description: Changing of f3 and f4 turns c1 to another animal.
events.conclusion: Changing f2, f3 or f4 mostly does not lead to turning c1 in c2 or c3. f1 and f2 have the most impact on changing c1 to c2 or to c3. Overall no feature at once has big impact on c1.

events.insight: Increasing f3 has no impact on c1.
Decreasing f3 has no impact on c1.

events.outcome: Increasing f3 from 9 to 14 does not change c1 to another class. Decreasing f3 from 9 to 0 turns c1 to c3.
events.insight: c1 can be classified as c3 if f3 value is drastically decreased.

events.outcome: Increasing f4 from 2 to 14 changes c1 to c3.
events.insight: f4 has impact on c1.

events.outcome: Decreasing f4 from 14 to 0 does not lead to change of c1 to c2 or to c3.
events.insight: Random point, not an outlier, must be inspected.
Changing values of f4 has no impact on c1.
Changing two values simultaneously can change point class.

events.description: If Detective Stories is high, it must be a Cat.
events.conclusion: Changing f4 in most cases has no impact on defining c2, thus f4 not necessarily must be high for a cat.

events.description: If art is less than 7, gardening is larger than 5, then it must be a dog.
events.conclusion: Hypothesis is confirmed: a smaller value than 7 of art and a bigger value than 5 of running can change point class to dog with high probability.

events.description: Smaller values of Swimming and Running decrease probability that a point belongs to a Duck class.
events.conclusion: Overall it can be seen, that decreasing Running and Swimming values lead to changing Duck class of the point to another one.

events.insight: It was expected, that probability of Duck class decreases, but it didn't happen.
In every prediction step object class is changed due to decreasing Swimming and Running values.
